.TH "waybar-dwl-tags" "5" "2026-03-23"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
waybar - dwl tags module
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \fBtags\fR module displays the current state of tags in dwl.\&
.PP
.SH CONFIGURATION
.PP
Addressed by \fBdwl/tags\fR
.PP
\fBnum-tags\fR: 
.br
typeof: uint 
.br
default: 9 
.br
The number of tags that should be displayed.\& Max 32.\&
.PP
\fBtag-labels\fR: 
.br
typeof: array 
.br
The label to display for each tag.\&
.PP
\fBdisable-click\fR: 
.br
typeof: bool 
.br
default: false 
.br
If set to false, you can left-click to set focused tag.\& Right-click to toggle tag focus.\& If set to true this behaviour is disabled.\&
.PP
\fBexpand\fR: 
.br
typeof: bool 
.br
default: false 
.br
Enables this module to consume all left over space dynamically.\&
.PP
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
"dwl/tags": {
	"num-tags": 5
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
.SH STYLE
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
\fB#tags button\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fB#tags button.\&occupied\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fB#tags button.\&empty\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fB#tags button.\&focused\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fB#tags button.\&urgent\fR
.PD
.PP
Note that occupied/focused/urgent status may overlap.\& That is, a tag may be
both occupied and focused at the same time.\&
.PP
